              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:πλανάω&lt;SDBG:πλανάω:000001&gt;}[b] ‘to wander about,’ {D:15.24}) one who or that which wanders about or around</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>wanderer</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:06500101300018} there appears to be a double-entendre in that πλανήτης may also suggest the meaning of {L:πλανάω&lt;SDBG:πλανάω:000000&gt;} ‘to deceive, to cause to be mistaken’ (see {D:31.8}). Therefore, such persons may be described not only as ‘wanderers,’ but as ‘deceivers.’ For a further discussion of πλανήτης in {S:06500101300018}, see {D:1.30}.</Comments>
